\section{Worked Example: Muon (Tetrahedral Cage)}

r_1 = 0.618 d_0 = 0.618 × 1.616 × 10^{-35} m ≈ 1.0 × 10^{-35} m.

k = SSV_0 / d_0^2 ≈ 1.63 × 10^7 / (1.616 × 10^{-35})^2 ≈ 6.24 × 10^{77} N/m.

μ_1 = 4 × 2.176 × 10^{-8} kg ≈ 8.704 × 10^{-8} kg.

ω_1 = √(k / μ_1) ≈ √(6.24 × 10^{77} / 8.704 × 10^{-8}) ≈ √(7.17 × 10^{84}) ≈ 8.47 × 10^{42} rad/s.

f_1 = ω_1 / 2π ≈ 1.35 × 10^{42} Hz.

m_μ c^2 = (1/2) ℏ (2π f_1) ≈ (1/2) × 1.054 × 10^{-34} × 2π × 1.35 × 10^{42} ≈ 4.47 × 10^8 MeV (predicted; observed 105.66 MeV, 4.23 × 10^6\% error—refinement via chiral tilt and multi-modes expected to reduce by factors of 10^6 in Paper 6).

